Metadata: Eunicenones A and B: diterpenoid cyclohexenones of a rare skeletal class from a new species of the Caribbean Gorgonian "Eunicea"

A new "Eunicea" species collected in the Tobago Cays, eastern Caribbean Sea, is chemically distinct from all other members of this genus. It yielded eunicenones A and B, compounds of a mixed biosynthetic origin. The new compounds are diterpenoid cyclohexenones of a new skeletal class related in part to the linear diterpenoid-​substituted quinones and hydroquinones isolated from various plants and animals.
